          <div class="content2">
            <h1>WHY IS STEM IMPORTANT?</h1>
            <p>In the future the majority of jobs will increasingly require
              STEM skills. Yet considerably less gilrs than boys approach STEM.
            </p>
            <p>Even though Women make half of the population, only 35% of STEM students
              in higher education globally are women, while the female representation in
              STEM careers is less than 30% (UNESCO)
            </p>
            <p>
              <b>Our Girls' education  programs seeks to break barriers including
              ending child marriage, FGM, teenage pregnancy, rape, teacher-student sexual
              relationship, access to scholarship and advance girls' right to education.</b>
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
